    "summary": "Ford Motor Co. reported a 5.5% decline in its U.S. February sales as it scales back EV offerings amid an anti-electric-vehicle policy environment. 149,962 Units Sold In February The automaker reported 149,962 units sold in the U.S. market during February, illustrating a 5.5% YoY decline from 2025's 158,675 figure, the company reported on Wednesday. Ford YTD sales were 285,324, 5.4% lower than 2025’s 301,619 units sold. The company, however, recorded more than a 30% uptick in its large SUV sales.",
